 jean x hu cfo products integrated circuits revenue us billion   net income us million   total assets us billion   total equity us billion   number of employees   website wwwmarvellcom marvells development center in petah tikva israel marvell technology group limited is a producer of storage communications and consumer semiconductor products the company was founded in  and has approximately  employees marvells us operating headquarters is located in santa clara california and the company operates design centers in places including canada europe israel india singapore and china marvell is a fabless manufacturer of semiconductors meaning that it is active entirely in core competencies of engineering and design with the actual manufacturing outsourced to contract manufacturers in lowercost emerging markets that ships more than one billion integrated circuits known as chips per year its market segments include the enterprise cloud automotive industrial and consumer markets contents  history  acquisitions  products  ethernet  xscale  sheevaplug  iphone  mmh  chromecast  legal cases  stock options  patent infringement  see also  references  external links historyedit marvell was founded in  by sehat sutardja his wife weili dai and brother pantas sutardja the initial public offering on june   near the end of the dotcom bubble raised  million with the stock listed on nasdaq with the symbol mrvl after quickly raising from  to over  per share three days later it was  at the time the five largest customers samsung electronics hitachi seagate technology fujitsu and toshiba accounted for  of sales the shares dropped sharply in december when insiders were allowed to sell the company is officially headquartered in hamilton bermuda the us operations known as marvell semiconductor incorporated are located in silicon valley california acquisitionsedit through the years marvell acquired smaller companies to enter new markets date acquired company expertise cost october  galileo technology ethernet switches system controllers m in stock june  syskonnect pc networking february  radlan embedded networking software m august  hard disk controller division of qlogic hard disk  tape drive controllers m in cash  m in stock december  soc division of utstarcom wireless communications g m in cash february  printer asic business of avago printer asics m in cash july  xscale product line from intel communications processors and socs m in cash january  picomobile networks communication software for iwlan and ims august  diseño de sistemas en silicio sa ds spanish company plc communication ics january  xelerated network processors marvells operating headquarters in santa clara productsedit main article list of marvell technology group chipsets marvell yukon gigabit ethernet controller in a sony vaio fw series laptop ethernetedit marvells first products were sold for computer data storage devices in march  computer networking products for the ethernet family were first shipped in october  the yukon brand gigabit ethernet controller was announced xscaleedit on june   the sale of intels xscale assets was announced intel agreed to sell the xscale business to marvell for an estimated usd  million in cash and the assumption of unspecified liabilities the acquisition was completed on november   sheevaplugedit in  marvell announced that the sheevaplug a small lowpower socbased arm architecture computer would be released with full schematicsclarification needed iphoneedit marvell supplied the wifi chip for the original firstgeneration apple iphone mmhedit marvell mobile hotspot mmh is an incar wifi connectivity the  audi a was the first automobile in the market to feature a factoryinstalled mmh chromecastedit googles chromecast products are powered by marvell socs namely the marvell armada  mini soc de for the chromecast st gen and marvell armada  mini plus soc de for the chromecast nd gen  chromecast audio in  marvell was named one of thomson reuters top  global innovators legal casesedit stock optionsedit in  the us securities and exchange commission sec started an inquiry on the companys stock option grant practices an investigation determined grant dates were chosen with the benefit of hindsight to make the options more valuable the press estimated that the founders and other executives had made  million in gains from the options which were awarded by the founding couple sehat sutardja and weili dai the sec asked to interview the company general counsel matthew gloss but marvell claimed attorneyclient privilege gloss was fired just before the investigation results were announced in may  abraham david sofaer was hired to investigate the investigation after gloss alleged it was not independent in announcing the results of its own inquiry the sec did not give marvell the credit granted other companies in the options scandal for cooperating with the sec’s investigation or for cleaning up  at the time of the announcement the coacting regional director of the sec’s san francisco office stated among other things that the sec did not believe that the lack of cooperation and remediation shown by marvell merited a whole lot of credit in terms of giving marvell a break  in announcing its results the sec found that gloss was not a participant in dai and sutardja’s backdating scheme marvell restated its financial results and stated that dai will no longer be executive vice president chief operating officer and a director but continue with the company in a nonmanagement position the company agreed to pay a  million fine in  but did not fire dai nor replace sutardja as chairman as stated by the investigating committee patent infringementedit in december  a pittsburgh jury ruled that marvell had infringed two patents coinventors alek kavcic and jose moura by incorporating hard disk technology developed and owned by carnegie mellon university without a license the technology relating to improving hard disk data read accuracy at high speeds was reported to have been used in  billion chips sold by marvell between  and  the jury awarded damages of  billion the third largest ever in a patent case at the time the jury also found that the breach had been willful giving the judge discretion to award up to three times the original damage amount in december  the company lost its mistrial bid in this dispute posttrial hearings were scheduled for may  and marvell reported to be considering an appeal in the interim in august us district judge nora barry fischer upheld the award on february   marvell agreed to a settlement in which marvell will pay carnegie mellon university  see alsoedit san francisco bay area portal companies portal list of marvell technology group chipsets marvell software solutions israel referencesedit  a b c d marvell  fiscal year results marvell retrieved  august    httpwwwmarvellcomcompany  a b company marvell retrieved on   sehat sutardja from radio boy to ceo the jakarta post  retrieved    suzanne herel june   meet the boss weili dai marvell technology group san francisco chronicle retrieved august     a b marvell technology group ltd mvrl company ipo overview nasdaq june    missing or empty url help accessdate requires url help  matthew richards july   two ipos wake up tech sector forbes retrieved august     a b c prospectus marvell technology group ltd june   retrieved august     marvell technologys shares drop sharply december   retrieved august     marvell to acquire lanchip supplier galileo for  billion in stock eetimes  retrieved    marvell acquires syskonnect gmbh for  gbps clientside silicon convergedigestcom  retrieved    marvell acquires radlan edncom  retrieved    marvell to acquire the hard disk drive controller business of qlogic marvell  retrieved    marvell acquires utstarcoms soc division evertiqcom  retrieved    marvell acquires avagos printer asics business insidchipscom december  retrieved    marvell technology group acquires avago for  million dealipediacom  retrieved  